cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.HC. 

This paper is about using human brain signals to accelerate reinforcement learning for robotic agents. The primary focus is on robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) since the goal is to improve the learning process for robots. The method proposed involves using supervised learning to decode EEG signals, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the use of human brain signals to shape robot behavior is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
